## 8. API Reference

### 8.1 Authentication
POST /api/v1/auth/login
Request: {username, password}
Response: {access_token, token_type, user_profile}
Dev mode: username=emp_no, password=dept
Prod mode: username=ldap_username, password=ldap_password

### 8.2 User Info
GET /api/v1/me/capabilities
Returns: {user_id, name, roles, collections, collection_agents}
Requires: Bearer token

GET /api/v1/me/chat/welcome?collection=RMS
Returns: {collection, personas, header_label, welcome_message}
Requires: Bearer token

### 8.3 Timesheet
GET /api/v1/me/timesheet
Returns: {tasks: [...], worklogs: [...]}
Filtered by user's personas (approver sees all, filler sees own)
Requires: Bearer token

POST /api/v1/me/timesheet/worklog/{worklog_id}/decision
Body: {decision: "APPROVED"|"REJECTED"}
Requires: Bearer token with approver persona

### 8.4 Chat
POST /api/v1/chat/stream
Body: 
  Normal message: {collection_name, message, chat_history (optional)}
  Form submission: {collection_name, form_submission: {form_id, data}}
Response: SSE stream of:
  {"type": "meta", "thread_id": "..."}
  {"type": "chunk", "text": "..."}     (text response)
  {"type": "form", "form_spec": {...}}  (form to render)
  "data: [DONE]"
Requires: Bearer token

## 9. Intent Routing

How parse_intent_node works:
1. Read most recent HumanMessage from state["messages"]
2. Lowercase the content
3. Check keywords in priority order: APPROVER > CREATOR > FILLER > QUERY
4. QUERY intent routes to user's highest persona (approver > creator > reviewer)
5. Default (no keywords matched): reviewer (filler)
6. If explicit agent_role provided AND user has it: prefer that
7. Result set in state["selected_agent_role"]

Document the full keyword priority table.

## 10. Conversation Memory

How it works:
- Frontend keeps conversationHistory[] array in JS (session-scoped)
- On each message send: slice last 10 items, include in request as chat_history
- Backend prepends to state["messages"] as HumanMessage/AIMessage before LLM call
- Agent nodes send [SystemMessage] + list(messages) to LLM (not just last message)
- Memory reset: on chat close (Back button), on agent switch, on logout
- Memory does NOT persist across page reloads (no DB persistence yet)

Note: Chat history persistence to DB is PENDING (chat_sessions, 
chat_messages tables not yet implemented).

